Very nice change of pace for filet. I followed the advice others did and increased orange and fennel, and decreased salt. what's nice is that it doesn't overpower a good piece of meat, just gives it a different slant. Easy too.

Rating: 3
Very tasty, with these minor adjustments: I heeded the wisdom of reviewers who said the crust was too salty and reduced the salt by 1/2 and still found it to be a little too salty for my taste. So next time I will use maybe 1/3 the required salt. I also added extra zest and a little extra crushed fennel seed, and I found the flavors/aromas more satisfying that way. I served this with haricot verts w/ shallot-mustard dressing and a potato-leek gratin for New Years dinner. Guests loved it.

