Following the cooking times exactly produced a perfectly cooked (medium rare, on the rare side) steak. Fabulous. Not sure about the crust though - it's DIFFERENT, to be sure, but fennel and steak seemed odd to pair. Would be good with fish, no doubt. And I found the crust/crumb topping to be WAY too salty. I eventually scraped it off - but my husband liked it and ate it all. AWESOME with the rosemary potato wedges. That recipe is a keeper.

